  "prompt": "How do you calculate credit hours earned?",
  "response": "Calculating credit hours earned typically involves looking at the courses you've completed and the credit value assigned to each course. Here\u2019s a step-by-step process to calculate the total credit hours you've earned:\n\n1. **Identify Completed Courses**: List all the courses you have successfully completed. This includes only those courses where you have received a passing grade.\n\n2. **Check Credit Hours per Course**: Each course at a college or university is usually assigned a certain number of credit hours. This information can typically be found in the course catalog or your transcript.\n\n3. **Sum the Credit Hours**: Add up the credit hours for all the completed courses. This sum is the total number of credit hours you have earned.\n\n4. **Consider Special Cases**:\n   - **Transfer Credits**: If you have transferred credits from another institution, ensure that they are included in your total. Each institution may have specific rules about how transfer credits are counted.\n   - **Labs, Recitals, or Practicals**: Some courses like labs or recitals might have different credit values or might be counted separately.\n   - **Pass/Fail Courses**: Courses taken on a pass/fail basis may count towards your total credit hours depending on your institution\u2019s policy.\n\n5. **Consult Your Academic Advisor**: If you are unsure about how certain credits are calculated or included, it\u2019s always a good idea to check with your academic advisor or registrar\u2019s office.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively calculate the total credit hours you have earned toward your degree.",
